title: Humphrey Bogart - Black Legion - 1937 - DVDRip
description:
This is one of Bogart's early films.

Frank Taylor is an average hard-working guy in a machine shop with ambitions to become foreman. But when the job opens, it is given to Joe Dombrowski, a Polish-American immigrant who spends his free time reading technical books on the workings of a drill press rather than socializing with other workers. Frank becomes disgruntled and is easily recruited by a co-worker to join the Black Legion, a secretive hate group similar to the Ku Klux Klan, which appeals to the xenophobic fears of its members and uses violence to intimidate foreign-born Americans.

Director:
Archie Mayo
